---
import { getLangFromUrl, useTranslations } from '../i18n/utils';

const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
const t = useTranslations(lang);

const experiences = {
  es: [
    {
      role: 'Data Engineer',
      company: 'Moni',
      period: 'Actualidad',
      type: 'current',
      bullets: [
        'Diseñé, desarrollé y documenté de cero 2 pipelines críticos sobre los ~20 DAGs en producción: el de mora total (orquesta un modelo dbt y envía la salida a S3 e Intiza en formatos específicos) y el de comunicaciones con clientes (ingesta raw vía API de Intercom + capa limpia para consumo de un LLM).',
        'Mantengo y documento el resto del stack de orquestación: ~20 DAGs en Apache Airflow corriendo sobre infraestructura ECS/Fargate.',
        'Diseñé y desarrollé el modelo Invoices en dbt (incluyendo tests) y el modelo de Débitos, dentro de un proyecto compartido de ~10 modelos core (loans_flow, quotas_flow, customers, quotas_collection, etc).',
        'Sumé KPIs de mora a las tablas de cobranzas y nuevos campos a las tablas de marketing, habilitando análisis que antes requerían queries ad-hoc.',
        'Optimicé ~10 tableros de Tableau migrando data sources a extractos y moviendo cálculos pesados a la fuente de datos, mejorando tiempos de carga para los equipos de negocio.',
      ],
      tags: ['Python', 'SQL', 'Apache Airflow', 'dbt', 'AWS', 'S3', 'ECS/Fargate', 'Tableau', 'Intercom API'],
    },
    {
      role: 'Data Engineer & Analyst',
      company: 'Ministerio de Obras Públicas de la Nación',
      period: '2020 – 2024',
      type: 'past',
      bullets: [
        'Desarrollé scripts en Python (Pandas, GeoPandas) para extracción, transformación y normalización de geodatos complejos a shapefiles.',
        'Mantuve y actualicé datasets en un Data Warehouse sobre SQL Server usando PL/SQL y Python.',
        'Diseñé y desarrollé tableros y modelos de datos en SQL para la Secretaría de Gestión de Obras y Proyectos, usados como herramienta de control de gestión.',
        'Construí una herramienta de procesamiento batch de imágenes (img-crop) para redimensionar y estructurar fotos antes de subirlas a mapainversiones.obraspublicas.gob.ar.',
      ],
      tags: ['Python', 'Pandas', 'GeoPandas', 'SQL Server', 'PL/SQL', 'Tableau', 'GIS'],
    },
    {
      role: 'Operador de Datos SIG',
      company: 'Dirección Provincial de Estadística',
      period: 'Feb 2020 – Sept 2020',
      type: 'past',
      bullets: [
        'Gestión de carga de datos y actualización de cartografía mediante ArcGIS 10.2.',
      ],
      tags: ['ArcGIS', 'SIG', 'Cartografía'],
    },
  ],
  en: [
    {
      role: 'Data Engineer',
      company: 'Moni',
      period: 'Present',
      type: 'current',
      bullets: [
        'Designed, built, and documented from scratch 2 critical pipelines on top of ~20 production DAGs: a total delinquency pipeline (orchestrates a dbt model and delivers output to S3 and Intiza in specific formats) and a customer communications pipeline (raw ingestion via Intercom API + clean layer for LLM consumption).',
        'Maintain and document the full orchestration stack: ~20 Apache Airflow DAGs running on ECS/Fargate infrastructure.',
        'Designed and built the Invoices dbt model (including tests) and the Debits model, within a shared project of ~10 core models (loans_flow, quotas_flow, customers, quotas_collection, etc).',
        'Added delinquency KPIs to collections tables and new fields to marketing tables, enabling analyses that previously required ad-hoc queries.',
        'Optimized ~10 Tableau dashboards by migrating data sources to extracts and pushing heavy calculations to the data source, improving load times for business teams.',
      ],
      tags: ['Python', 'SQL', 'Apache Airflow', 'dbt', 'AWS', 'S3', 'ECS/Fargate', 'Tableau', 'Intercom API'],
    },
    {
      role: 'Data Engineer & Analyst',
      company: 'National Ministry of Public Works',
      period: '2020 – 2024',
      type: 'past',
      bullets: [
        'Developed Python scripts (Pandas, GeoPandas) for extraction, transformation, and normalization of complex geodata into shapefiles.',
        'Maintained and updated datasets in a Data Warehouse on SQL Server using PL/SQL and Python.',
        'Designed and built SQL data models and control dashboards for the Secretariat of Works Management, used as a management control tool.',
        'Built a batch image processing tool (img-crop) to resize and structure photos before uploading them to mapainversiones.obraspublicas.gob.ar.',
      ],
      tags: ['Python', 'Pandas', 'GeoPandas', 'SQL Server', 'PL/SQL', 'Tableau', 'GIS'],
    },
    {
      role: 'GIS Data Operator',
      company: 'Provincial Directorate of Statistics',
      period: 'Feb 2020 – Sept 2020',
      type: 'past',
      bullets: [
        'Managed data upload workflows and cartography updates using ArcGIS 10.2.',
      ],
      tags: ['ArcGIS', 'GIS', 'Cartography'],
    },
  ],
};

const items = experiences[lang];
---

<section class="experience-section" id="experience">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">{t('experience.title')}</h2>

    <div class="timeline">
      {items.map((exp, i) => (
        <div class={`timeline-item ${exp.type}`}>
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <div class="dot"></div>
            {i < items.length - 1 && <div class="line"></div>}
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-card glass">
            <div class="card-header">
              <div>
                <h3 class="role">{exp.role}</h3>
                <p class="company">{exp.company}</p>
              </div>
              <span class={`period mono ${exp.type === 'current' ? 'period-current' : ''}`}>
                {exp.period}
              </span>
            </div>
            <ul class="bullets">
              {exp.bullets.map(b => (
                <li>{b}</li>
              ))}
            </ul>
            <div class="exp-tags">
              {exp.tags.map(tag => (
                <span class="exp-tag">{tag}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .experience-section {
    padding: 6rem 0;
  }

  .timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .timeline-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .timeline-marker {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .dot {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-border);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: var(--transition);
  }

  .timeline-item.current .dot {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    border-color: var(--color-primary);
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary-glow);
  }

  .line {
    width: 2px;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--color-border);
    margin-top: 6px;
    min-height: 40px;
  }

  .timeline-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    transition: var(--transition);
  }

  .timeline-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(0, 255, 204, 0.2);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .card-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .role {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .company {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .period {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-hover);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  .period-current {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-primary);
    background: var(--color-primary-glow);
  }

  .bullets {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .bullets li {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .bullets li::before {
    content: '▸';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    top: 0.15rem;
  }

  .exp-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .exp-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .timeline-item {
      grid-template-columns: 24px 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
